title: Twin Bing Classic Road Race
description: The Twin Bing Road Race is an A and B category road race starting in the very small town of Climbing Hill, Iowa.
course:
The race will leave Climbing Hill proceding west to Old Highway 141, north to county road D-38, east past Bronson to the Moville Blacktop, south back to Climbing Hill and will finish atop the \\\"Climbing Hill\\\" that overlooks the town. 

There is a wide mix of terrain from flats to easy rollers to big rollers and some hard climbs.
registration:
Day-of registration at Climbing Hill. No late fee.
race A begins at 10 am race B begins at 10:15 am registration closing 15 minutes before each race
notes:
Yellow Line rule enforced. Wheels in, wheels out. 
Climbing Hill is very small. Don\\\'t assume there will be  water, bathrooms and food readily available. There is a local cafe but it may not be open this time of year. The nearest larger towns are Moville and Sergeant Buff if you need gas and groceries and somewhere to eat. Bronson has a small grocery store.
directions:
(Accurate directions from I-29 and Highway 20 to follow.)

title: Clear Lake Bicycle Blues and BBQ Criterium
Clear Lake Bicycle Blues and BBQ Road Race
Grinnell Twilight Criterium
description:
The Grinnell Twilight Criterium

	We are having a bike race in Downtown Grinnell!  It will be held Saturday August 8th.  A criterium is a multiple lap race on a short course.  The course is located in our beautiful downtown.
course: It will be approximately one kilometer in length and is L shaped with six turns.  It starts and finishes on Broad Street, the racers will wind their way through the Main St. and Commercial Ave. to finally ride around Central Park to return to the finish line.  There will groups racing from more and less experienced levels separated in five categories: juniors (18 years old and younger riders), women with more experience racing and less experience.  There will be races men in these same experience levels.  To participate cyclists must have USAC licenses.  The races will start at 4 p.m. and go until twilight.
registration:
Send $20 registration fee to
Bikes To You
921 Broad St
Grinnell, Iowa 50112
Late entry fee $5 after 7/31/09
notes:
Held Under USCF permit
Therefore all races will be held in accordance with USAC rules.
